            (Police-constable C 158.) I took<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183209060068"></xptr>the prisoner - in going along she told her mother that she stole a spoon, pawned it for 1s. 3d., and tore the ticket up - I said, "What is that she says?" the mother said, "I could not rightly hear;" I said, "You must be a wicked woman;" the prisoner said, "I stole a spoon, pawned it for 1s. 3d., and tore the ticket up:" "Yes, (said she) she did."</p>
               <p>GUILTY. Aged 13.</p>
